      "raw_text": "Lawyers, politicians, councilmen\nand people generally, all interested in\nthe question of submitting the char\nter amendment to the people next\nelection, were I'm Judge Remnants\ncourt this morning to listen to the\nbattle over the application of w. w.\nHindman for a writ of mandate to\ncompel the city council to publish\nthe amendment submitting franchises\nto the vote of the people, so that it\ncan be voted upon at the coming city\nelection.\n\n\nOne peculiar phase of the fight over\nthe franchises at this time is the\nunanimity with which the corpora\nton lawyers are lined up against the\napplication.\n\n\nWhen House Bill so\" was first in\ntroduced in the Legislature all of the\ncorporation henchmen were ostensi-\nbly, working for the bill-and this in\ncluded the Washington Water Power"
